                                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.&#8212;<name type="person" key="xx">Private Milford Clark</name>, <name type="organization" key="xx">Co. C, 125th New
                                                                York Volunteers</name>, aged 20 years, was wounded at
                                                  <name type="BATTLE" key="3"><choice><orig>Spottsylvania</orig><reg>Spotsylvania</reg></choice>, Virginia</name>, <date type="injury" when="1864-05-18">May 18th, 1864</date>, by a
                                                  conoidal ball, which struck the cranium half an
                                                  inch above the frontal eminence, and passed
                                                  posteriorly four inches, lacerating the scalp in
                                                  its course.  He was admitted into the 1st division,
                                                                  Second Corps, hospital on <date type="admit" when="1864-05-18">the same day</date>, and thence
                                                                sent to the <name type="hospital" key="171">Armory Square Hospital</name> Washington, on
                                                                <date type="transfer" when="1864-05-28">the 28th</date>, where the wound was carefully examined
                                                  and a fissure of the outer table one inch in
                                                  length, discovered.  The operation of trephining
                                                  was <date type="operation" when="1864-05-28">at once</date> instituted, and the depressed portion
                                                  of the inner table elevated.  Death, preceded by
                                                  coma, however, ensued on <date type="death" when="1864-06-25">June 25th</date>.   <name type="person" key="123">Surgeon D. W. Bliss</name>, <name type="organization" key="132">U. S. V.</name>, reports the case.</p>                                                
